# Decap CMS GitHub OAuth Configuration
# These environment variables are required for the CMS admin panel to work on Cloudflare Pages

# GitHub OAuth App Credentials
# Get these from: https://github.com/settings/developers
OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_client_id_here
OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_client_secret_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a GitHub OAuth app at https://github.com/settings/developers
# 2. Set the callback URL to: https://api.netlify.com/auth/done
# 3. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret
# 4. Add these as environment variables in Cloudflare Pages:
#    - Go to: Cloudflare Dashboard → Pages → Your Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Add both variables for Production and Preview environments
# 5. DO NOT commit this file with real values to Git!

# For local development:
# - Copy this file to .env
# - Fill in your actual values
# - Run: npx decap-server (in one terminal)
# - Run: npm run dev (in another terminal)
# - Access: http://localhost:4321/admin

